ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-bundle_msgs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

If set to 1, combines multiple RSVP messages into a single PDU to reduce processing overhead and bandwidth consumption. If set to 0, does not combine messages. refresh_reduction, reliable_delivery, summary_refresh, and bundle_msgs work together. If anyone of them is turned on, all the options are enabled.

DEFAULT

 None

-count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Number of RSVP sessions to create on the interface.

DEFAULT

 None

-egress_label_mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

Specifies the label advertisement for the egress of an LSP as one of nextlabel - Advertises the next available label.exnull - Advertises label 9, the explicit null label.imnull - Advertises label 3, the implicit null label.

DEFAULT

 None

-graceful_restart

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.If true (1), enable graceful restart which adds RESTART_CAP object in Hello messages. Enable this will enable hello_msgs automatically.

DEFAULT

 None

-graceful_restart_recovery_time

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Recovery Time ( in ms ). Minimum value 0 ms. Ixia will wait for this configured interval for the DUT to help it recover the egress LSPs. If no recovery label is received from the DUT within this time, those Egress LSPs would be treated as having time-outed i.e. labels will be removed. If 0 Recovery-time is configured, then the restarting Ixia side will tear down its Egress sessions as soon as the Restart period ends, but no Resv Tear message will be sent.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1 AND the graceful_restarts_number value is greater than 1

DEFAULT

 None

-graceful_restart_restart_time

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Restart Start Time in ms. Minimum value 100 ms ( Immediate Restart ).We will stop sending Hellos after this timer gets fired, from the time the Neighborship comes up.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1.

DEFAULT

 None

-graceful_restart_up_time

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Restart Up time in ms. Minimum value 50 ms. After the Restarting time is over, Ixia will wait for this configured interval before trying to repeat the Restart cycle. This is effective only untill the number of restarts is not equal to the user-configured number of Graceful Restart cycles. After that Ixia will not take any action to being down a Neighborship on its own.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1 AND the graceful_restarts_count value is greater than 1

DEFAULT

 None

-graceful_restarts_count

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Number of Restart. The number of times the Ixia emulated RSVP neighbor will move to Restarting / Recovering and Up states before stopping the cycle.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1

DEFAULT

 None

-hello_tlvs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Generalized TLV messages that are included with all HELLO. Allows the user to custom-configure the optional Hello extension for sending Hello Messages between immediate RSVP neighbors - for determining reachability. The Hello extension contains a Hello message (Class Type = 20), a Hello Request object, and a Hello Ack object, as specified in RFC 3209. Struct of form class,cType,data:class,cType,data:...Example: "22,1,aa:22,2,bb:23,2,13"class = The class distinguisher of the TLV. The HELLO class is 22.cType = The C-Type distinguisher of the TLV. The C_Type of the included Object. C_Type 1 = Hello Request; C_Type 2 = Hello Acknowledgement.data = The data associated with the TLV. The length of the TLV will be calculated from the length of this data. One 32-bit Source Instance plus one 32-bit Destination Instance for each object: For the Hello Request, the instance value is changed due to sender reset or reboot, or when link to the neighbor is down. It must not be set to 0. For the Hello Ack, the most recent instance value received from the neighbor. It must = 0 if no instance value has ever been received from that neighbor.When -mode is create and -count > 1 the value of this parameter will be set on ALL neighbor pairs created.When -mode is modify and a list of handles is passed to -handle parameter: if hello_tlvs is a list of parameters, it must either have the same length as the list of handles and each hello_tlv value from the list will be set on the according rsvp handle; if hello_tlvs is a single value, it will be set on ALL handles from the handle list. Trying to modify this parameter will overwrite previous values.

DEFAULT

 None

-override_existence_check

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

If this option is enabled, the interface existence check is skipped but the list of interfaces is still created and maintained in order to keep track of existing interfaces if required. Using this option will speed up the creation of the interfaces.

DEFAULT

0

-override_tracking

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

If this option is enabled, the list of interfaces will no longer be created and maintained, thus speeding up the creation of interfaces even more. Also, it will enable -override_existence_check in case it was not already enabled because checking for interface existence becomes impossible if the list of interfaces does not exist anymore.

DEFAULT

0

bundle_msgs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

DESCRIPTION

If set to 1, combines multiple RSVP messages into a single PDU to reduce processing overhead and bandwidth consumption. If set to 0, does not combine messages. refresh_reduction, reliable_delivery, summary_refresh, and bundle_msgs work together. If anyone of them is turned on, all the options are enabled.

graceful_restart_recovery_time

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Recovery Time ( in ms ). Minimum value 0 ms. Ixia will wait for this configured interval for the DUT to help it recover the egress LSPs. If no recovery label is received from the DUT within this time, those Egress LSPs would be treated as having time-outed i.e. labels will be removed. If 0 Recovery-time is configured, then the restarting Ixia side will tear down its Egress sessions as soon as the Restart period ends, but no Resv Tear message will be sent.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1 AND the graceful_restarts_number value is greater than 1

DEFAULT

hello_tlvs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Generalized TLV messages that are included with all HELLO. Allows the user to custom-configure the optional Hello extension for sending Hello Messages between immediate RSVP neighbors - for determining reachability. The Hello extension contains a Hello message (Class Type = 20), a Hello Request object, and a Hello Ack object, as specified in RFC 3209. Struct of form class,cType,data:class,cType,data:...Example: "22,1,aa:22,2,bb:23,2,13"class = The class distinguisher of the TLV. The HELLO class is 22.cType = The C-Type distinguisher of the TLV. The C_Type of the included Object. C_Type 1 = Hello Request; C_Type 2 = Hello Acknowledgement.data = The data associated with the TLV. The length of the TLV will be calculated from the length of this data. One 32-bit Source Instance plus one 32-bit Destination Instance for each object: For the Hello Request, the instance value is changed due to sender reset or reboot, or when link to the neighbor is down. It must not be set to 0. For the Hello Ack, the most recent instance value received from the neighbor. It must = 0 if no instance value has ever been received from that neighbor.When -mode is create and -count > 1 the value of this parameter will be set on ALL neighbor pairs created.When -mode is modify and a list of handles is passed to -handle parameter: if hello_tlvs is a list of parameters, it must either have the same length as the list of handles and each hello_tlv value from the list will be set on the according rsvp handle; if hello_tlvs is a single value, it will be set on ALL handles from the handle list. Trying to modify this parameter will overwrite previous values.

DEFAULT

 None

graceful_restart_recovery_time

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Recovery Time ( in ms ). Minimum value 0 ms. Ixia will wait for this configured interval for the DUT to help it recover the egress LSPs. If no recovery label is received from the DUT within this time, those Egress LSPs would be treated as having time-outed i.e. labels will be removed. If 0 Recovery-time is configured, then the restarting Ixia side will tear down its Egress sessions as soon as the Restart period ends, but no Resv Tear message will be sent.This parameter is valid only when -graceful_restart is 1 AND the graceful_restarts_number value is greater than 1

hello_tlvs

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Available only with IxTclNetwork.Generalized TLV messages that are included with all HELLO. Allows the user to custom-configure the optional Hello extension for sending Hello Messages between immediate RSVP neighbors - for determining reachability. The Hello extension contains a Hello message (Class Type = 20), a Hello Request object, and a Hello Ack object, as specified in RFC 3209. Struct of form class,cType,data:class,cType,data:...Example: "22,1,aa:22,2,bb:23,2,13"class = The class distinguisher of the TLV. The HELLO class is 22.cType = The C-Type distinguisher of the TLV. The C_Type of the included Object. C_Type 1 = Hello Request; C_Type 2 = Hello Acknowledgement.data = The data associated with the TLV. The length of the TLV will be calculated from the length of this data. One 32-bit Source Instance plus one 32-bit Destination Instance for each object: For the Hello Request, the instance value is changed due to sender reset or reboot, or when link to the neighbor is down. It must not be set to 0. For the Hello Ack, the most recent instance value received from the neighbor. It must = 0 if no instance value has ever been received from that neighbor.When -mode is create and -count > 1 the value of this parameter will be set on ALL neighbor pairs created.When -mode is modify and a list of handles is passed to -handle parameter: if hello_tlvs is a list of parameters, it must either have the same length as the list of handles and each hello_tlv value from the list will be set on the according rsvp handle; if hello_tlvs is a single value, it will be set on ALL handles from the handle list. Trying to modify this parameter will overwrite previous values.

DEFAULT

 None
